the Trouble , which her Ruin cost
For Love , like mine , no cold Indifference bears ; It feeds on timorous Thoughts , and anxious Cares

ANTILOCHUS was he who caused my Pain : Or , if in borrowed Arms PATROCLUS bled , I wept , because his Craft no better sped : When Rhodian Blood had bathed the Lycian Spear , The Rhodian Youth again renewed my Care : In fine , whatever Graecian Chief was killed , My fearful Heart , like srigid Ice , was chilled ; Lest flattering Fame my doubtful Ears should cheat , And , for my Lord's , proclaim another's Fate : But Heaven , propitious to my chaste Desire , Preserved you safe , and Troy consumed with Fire

One stains a Table with the purple Draught , And shows the furious Battles , which you fought ; Paints , with the Wine , which from the Glass he pours , Camps , Rivers , Hills , and all the Trojan Towers : And , This , says he , is the Sigean Plain ; And here the silver Simois rolls his Train

the Camp of Foes you rove , Mindful of Wiles , forgetful of your Love

go Among the midnight Terrors of the Foe
go Among the midnight Terrors of the Foe
with Fear my trembling Bosom beat , To hear my Son your daring Deeds relate
my Son your daring Deeds relate
to your Camp , with Thracian Spoils adorned
my absent Lord , who wrought its Fall
to their Hands a Letter I impart , To give it you , the Partner of my Heart
kind to lead them to my absent Love
So kind to lead them to my absent Love
If Chance , or Destiny should ever prove
If Chance , or Destiny should ever prove
I should not then be singly cursed to cry
I what to hope , or what to fear
those Storms detain you on the Seas
chides me for my constant Flames : My constant Flames shall ever true remain ; Let Fathers chide , and Suitors court in vain
they come to seek your Crown , And feast
your Lambs , to grace the Suitor's Board

Your feeble Wife , your Father worn with Age , Your tender Son , too weak to cheque their Rage ; For whom they lately crafty Ambush laid , And menaced Death on his devoted Head ; When , mocking all their Stratagems
weak to chase the Foes away
young to bear the Regal Sway
An ancient Dame , unworthy of your Love
